# Phase Gate Discipline

## Principle

**Mid-phase:** narrow, fast checks while editing.
**Phase-end:** full gate matrix via `frontend-quality-enforcer` or lane verify command.

Do not run full E2E, release gates, or audit trio after every single file edit.

## Mid-phase checks (during implementation)

Allowed after substantive edits within a phase:

- `ReadLints` on touched files
- Narrow lint/typecheck on touched package (`eslint` scoped, `tsc --noEmit` if fast)
- Single component or section smoke when explicitly in P2/P3

## Phase-end gates (mandatory before phase sign-off)

Delegate to `frontend-quality-enforcer` or run lane bundle:

| Lane | Phase-end bundle |
|------|------------------|
| `web/` (frontend) | `npm run health:check` from `web/` |
| `web/src/server/`, `web/src/app/api/` (backend) | `@backend-quality-enforcer` via `/phase-gate-backend` |
| `Frontend_Nextjs/` | `pnpm build` + nextjs audit trio (+ parity if migration) |
| `sites/` | html-website-builder Final QA + audit trio subagents |

## Phase model (senior-frontend-specialist)

| Phase | Phase-end requirement |
|-------|----------------------|
| P0 Discovery | Scope doc on disk |
| P1 Tokens/DS | DS audit / contrast table |
| P2 Primitives | Component smoke |
| P3 Sections | a11y + perf subagents |
| P4 Integration | Integration smoke |
| P5 Verify | `@frontend-quality-enforcer` full matrix |

## Failure protocol

If phase-end gate fails: STOP → DEBUG → FIX → RE-RUN phase-end gates. Do not advance to next phase with red gates.

## Zero-gate rule interaction

Rule `60-zero-gate-health-check.mdc` still applies when **declaring work complete** for delivery. Phase discipline governs **when** to run heavy checks during multi-step work — not whether to skip them at completion.

**Exception — user requests push:** Always run full `npm run ci:check --prefix web` from repo root before push, regardless of phase. See `/pre-push-check` and rule `71-git-discipline.mdc`.
